			<div class="content" id="post-content-4854317">
									

<p>I don't really understand why this anomaly would ever be relinquished for the purposes identified in the logs. It seems like the scip would make for a <em>uniquely terrible</em> password due to its anomalous properties, and none of the other proposed uses make sense to me either. (That may be my fault as a reader.)</p>
<p>It was an enjoyable and entertaining read, and your inventiveness is admirable, but I feel obligated to novote the SCP, just because all the relinquishing seems like the opposite of containment. I personally think that experiments should only be conducted (a) when there's some concern about containment procedures potentially being insufficient, or (b) when a specific and explicitly identifiable beneficial result is predicted as the likely outcome (let me tell you about how I'm maybe the only reader who <em>doesn't</em> like the SCP-914 logs&#8230;).</p>

